Pages = {87350-87368},
Abstract = {Evaluating narrative visualizations is complex due to their dependence
   on user characteristics, context, and storytelling elements. This study
   presents NaVi-Q, a quality model designed to structure the assessment of
   narrative visualizations, drawing on principles from Software
   Engineering and Information Visualization. The model was tested in an
   experiment where 40 participants evaluated 30 visualizations. The
   results suggest that the model's criteria align with expert assessments
   in distinguishing different quality levels. Scores from experts and
   non-experts followed similar patterns, indicating that the model may be
   applicable across different levels of experience. These findings suggest
