   qualitative case studies, an extensive multinational survey in 16 EU
   countries, their re-use in scenario predictions, and their framing for
   developing interactive transition pathways for individuals and
   communities. With a strong geospatial focus and a narrative design, the
   tool promotes collaborative sensemaking processes of the real world
   instead of plain visualization. This paper addresses the development
   process, design choices, data integration strategies, architecture
   details, and deployment methods of the tool. We demonstrate how using
   collaborative and interactive dashboards can enhance the communication
