Abstract = {Data narratives are an emerging form of communication that employs
   enhanced media for effective knowledge transfer of complex information.
   Researchers in the fields of data visualization and artificial
   intelligence have begun to pioneer new structures of communication to
   improve the efficiency of construction and the retention of information
   provided by the knowledge transfer experience. In this paper, we report
   the results of an empirical study conducted to compare the performance
   of various narrative communication techniques including frame based
   narrative visualization, documentary narrative visualization, computer
   generated text narratives and human generated text narratives. We assess
   the knowledge transfer performance for each of these data driven
   narrative structures. Across all conditions, an identical set of
