Abstract = {This study quantifies the effectiveness of information recall with
   direct and indirect labeling of the annotation layer in a news data
   visualization. Variations of three data visualizations from The New York
   Times, The Washington Post, and The Wall Street Journal were presented
   to participants in a crowdsourced experiment to measure their story
   comprehension. Our results demonstrate that direct labeling offers no
